.TH "vm_map_pages_zero" 9 "vm_map_pages_zero" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vm_map_pages_zero \- map range of kernel pages starts with zero offset
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vm_map_pages_zero
.BI "(struct vm_area_struct *vma "  ","
.BI "struct page **pages "  ","
.BI "unsigned long num "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vma" 12
user vma to map to
.IP "pages" 12
pointer to array of source kernel pages
.IP "num" 12
number of pages in page array
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Similar to \fBvm_map_pages\fP, except that it explicitly sets the offset
to 0. This function is intended for the drivers that did not consider
vm_pgoff.
.SH "CONTEXT"
Process context. Called by mmap handlers.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success and error code otherwise.
